  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>When staying at Hotel Pontechiesa you'll be booked on half board, so you can enjoy breakfast and dinner each day.</p>
<p>Start the day off right with a great selection from the buffet where you will find plenty of options including eggs and bacon.</p>
<p>Dinner starts with a salad and vegetable buffet before being served 3 courses to your table. To end the meal it's back up to the buffet to help yourself to dessert and cheese.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>If you are searching for a charming, family run hotel in one of Italy's most prestigious resorts, look no further. Hotel Pontechiesa is the perfect choice where guests can enjoy the comfortable Alpine style rooms with fantastic views of the surrounding mountains while the staff look after your every need. </p>
<h2>Quiet location</h2>
<p>Hotel Pontechiesa's peaceful surroundings provide the perfect backdrop for a relaxing and restorative stay, allowing guests to fully disconnect and recharge amidst the beauty of the Dolomites. You're not too far from the centre of resort, so easy access when it comes to getting to the lifts, having a drink, doing a spot of shopping or eating out. </p>
<h2>Spa </h2>
<p>At the end of a ski day, there's nothing better than taking some time to treat yourself to the wellness area where you can sit back, close your eyes and give your body a well deserved break from tearing up the slopes. By paying locally, you can access the facilities which include a sauna, steam room, sensory shower and a relaxation area, perfect if you want to read a few chapters of your book.</p>
<h3>Exclusive to Inghams</h3>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with Hotel Pontechiesa the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>]]></description>
